---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import siteSettings from '../../../data/site-settings.json';
import { buildArticleSchema, buildBreadcrumbSchema, buildFAQSchema, buildWebSiteSchema } from '../../../lib/seo';

const title = 'RV water intrusion | How to recognize it and what to do';
const description = 'Clinique du VR guide to recognize water intrusion on an RV, travel trailer, or caravan and know what to do before the damage gets worse.';
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What are the first signs of water intrusion in an RV?',
    answer: 'The first signs are often a moisture smell, a water stain, a cracked seal, a warped ceiling, a soft wall, or a swelling floor.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What should I do first if I suspect water intrusion?',
    answer: 'Try to keep the vehicle away from more water exposure, take photos, note the affected areas, and then confirm whether the right next step is inspection, targeted maintenance, or repair.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does water intrusion always mean a major repair?',
    answer: 'Not always. If caught early, seal maintenance or a sealing correction may be enough. Once materials are already affected, repair becomes more likely.'
  }
];
const schemas = [
  buildWebSiteSchema(),
  buildArticleSchema({
    headline: title,
    description,
    path: '/en/resources/rv-water-intrusion/'
  }),
  buildFAQSchema(faqs),
  buildBreadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/en/' },
    { name: 'Resources' },
    { name: 'Water intrusion' }
  ])
];
---

<Layout
  title={`${title} | Clinique du VR`}
  description={description}
  lang="en-CA"
  canonicalPath="/en/resources/rv-water-intrusion/"
  frPath="/ressources/infiltration-eau-vr/"
  enPath="/en/resources/rv-water-intrusion/"
  schemas={schemas}
  ogType="article"
>
  <Header lang="en" />
  <main>
    <section class="interior-hero">
      <div class="container interior-hero-grid">
        <div class="interior-hero-copy">
          <p class="interior-eyebrow">Practical resource</p>
          <h1>RV water intrusion: how to recognize it and what to do</h1>
          <p class="interior-lead">Water intrusion on an RV or trailer does not always begin with a dramatic visible failure. More often, it starts with smaller warning signs that become serious if nothing is done.</p>
          <div class="hero-badges">
            <span>Warning signs first</span>
            <span>Inspection before guesswork</span>
            <span>Workshop guidance from Gatineau</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="interior-hero-card">
          <div class="interior-hero-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-droplet"></i>
          </div>
          <h2>What this guide helps you do</h2>
          <ul class="hero-checklist">
            <li>Spot the most common warning signs</li>
            <li>Avoid waiting too long before acting</li>
            <li>Choose between inspection, maintenance, and repair</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="interior-section">
      <div class="container interior-body-grid">
        <article class="interior-content-main">
          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>How to recognize water intrusion</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">The most common signs are a moisture smell, a water stain, dry or cracked seals, a warped surface, a soft wall, a swelling floor, or a section of ceiling that no longer looks right. On an RV, intrusion can also hide around openings, roof areas, corners, and trim.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card interior-card-alt">
            <h2>What to check first</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">Wall seals, roof seals, moldings, vulnerable openings, corners, window edges, roof vents, and the roof membrane are among the first places to look. These are often the areas that let water in before damage becomes obvious.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>What to do as soon as you suspect it</h2>
            <ol>
              <li>Keep the vehicle sheltered if possible.</li>
              <li>Take photos of visible signs.</li>
              <li>Do not wait for another storm or another season.</li>
              <li>Confirm whether the next useful step is inspection, seal maintenance, or repair.</li>
            </ol>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card interior-card-alt">
            <h2>What to avoid</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">It is better not to hide the symptom too quickly without confirming the real cause. Water intrusion that is poorly understood can continue behind surfaces and turn a still-limited issue into a much more expensive repair file.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>When inspection is the right first step</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">Inspection is often the best option when you suspect water intrusion but do not yet know where it is coming from, when several signs point in different directions, or when you want to confirm the vehicle’s actual condition before deciding on work.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card">
            <h2>When maintenance or repair takes over</h2>
            <p class="interior-copy">If the seals or roof mostly show early aging without major visible damage, maintenance may be enough. If water has already reached the materials and surfaces are soft or damaged, repair is usually the logical next step.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="interior-card interior-card-alt">
            <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
            <div class="interior-faq-list">
              {faqs.map((item) => (
                <details class="interior-faq-item">
                  <summary><h3>{item.question}</h3></summary>
                  <p>{item.answer}</p>
                </details>
              ))}
            </div>
          </section>
        </article>

        <aside class="interior-side-panel">
          <div class="interior-side-card interior-side-card-primary">
            <h3>Need a quick opinion?</h3>
            <p>We can point you toward inspection, maintenance, or repair depending on the level of water damage and what is already visible.</p>
            <a class="interior-side-button" href={`tel:${siteSettings.phone.href}`}>{siteSettings.phone.display}</a>
            <a class="interior-side-link" href={siteSettings.squareBookingUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book online</a>
          </div>

          <div class="interior-side-card">
            <h3>Related services</h3>
            <nav class="interior-service-nav" aria-label="Related services">
              <a href="/en/services/inspection/"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-check"></i><span>Inspection</span></a>
              <a href="/en/services/maintenance/"><i class="fas fa-screwdriver-wrench"></i><span>Maintenance</span></a>
              <a href="/en/services/repair/"><i class="fas fa-toolbox"></i><span>Repair</span></a>
              <a href="/en/realisations/"><i class="fas fa-images"></i><span>Projects</span></a>
            </nav>
          </div>

          <div class="interior-side-card">
            <h3>Service areas</h3>
            <nav class="interior-service-nav" aria-label="Service areas">
              <a href="/en/service-areas/"><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i><span>Outaouais</span></a>
              <a href="/en/service-areas/"><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i><span>Ottawa</span></a>
              <a href="/en/service-areas/"><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i><span>Laurentides</span></a>
            </nav>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer lang="en" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .interior-hero-copy h1 { max-width: 16ch; }
  .hero-badges { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.8rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .hero-badges span { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; min-height: 44px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 14px; background: var(--brand-gold); color: var(--brand-navy-dark); font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 10px 18px rgba(14, 31, 49, 0.14); }
  .hero-checklist { display: grid; gap: 0.65rem; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--brand-muted); }
  .interior-card ol { display: grid; gap: 0.85rem; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--brand-ink); }
  .interior-card li::marker, .hero-checklist li::marker { color: var(--brand-green); font-weight: 700; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-badges { gap: 0.55rem; }
    .hero-badges span { min-height: 38px; padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 12px; font-size: 0.88rem; }
  }
</style>
